From:         Kathryn Gandek <KGANDEK%MITVMC.BITNET@MITVMA.MIT.EDU>
Subject:      Woozy at the War

In reply to the gentle who inquired about ways to avoid suffering from
the heat while camping....

My lord who used to heavy list and now fences suffers greatly from heat
as well as sunburning more quickly than most people I have ever known.
The best solution we have for him is whenever he feels particularly hard
hit I empty the water from the ice bags in the cooler (maybe not period,
but definitely a sane thing to have) and splash it behind his ears, wrists
neck and then empty whatever is left over his head.  It works, but I always
thought it a bit odd until the Boredom War when I was running around as
list mistress and he caught me (who is usually fairly impervious to heat)
getting that heat glazed look.  Before I could protest, he doused me with a
healthy splash of the water.  It was such a temperature shock it almost hurt,
but it also snapped me out of it and made my body feel much cooler.

I don't suggest it for everyone, but if you can stand it (and don't mind
getting your garb wet) a preventative dose of that a couple of times during
the day might cool you down enough to take some of the strain off your body
so you can enjoy that nighttime revelling.

Catrin gan Mor Rhyd
