Message-Id: <Jun.21.14.47.39.1988.26440@straits.rutgers.edu>

Greetings good gentles.

The Knowne World Heraldic Symposium was held this past weekend in the
Barony of Forgotten Sea, Calontir.  The Laurel Queen of Arms, seven
Kingdom's Principal Heralds, and a dozen or so other members of the
College of Arms were present, as well as a host of other heralds from
Calontir, Ansteorra, the Middle, and elsewhere. (For me, the surprise
attendant was Koppel von Bayern, now living in Trimaris, and still an
active herald.  He was the second head herald of the East Kingdom,
before the office really had a title, back in AS 8 or so.  Alfgar, I
expect you'll be amused by this note.) 

The event was a great success, and I believe everyone enjoyed it.  In
addition to a day of classes on various heraldic subjects (including a
talk on Islamic Heraldry by Lord Da'ud ibn Auda, Star Principal
Herald), there were many discussions of revising the Rules for
Submissions and other issues facing the College of Arms.

There will probably be a new edition of the Rules for Submissions
published in early autumn.  These revised rules are a major
simplification of the existing rules, and should be much easier to
use for both heralds and non-heralds.  These rules will be published
in TI, and will be mass-mailed to every branch of the SCA, along with
other useful material for the local herald.

The lady Laurel also announced her intention to publish in TI a poll
of the populace, asking for input on an assortment of questions which
have been discussed at length over past years.  These questions will
cover such issues as the registration of household names and badges,
the registration of alternate personae, and the registration of
non-human names.  The idea will be to find out whether the opinions of
the College coincide with those of the populace, and if any changes
should be made on that basis.  

	Arval Benicoeur, Brigantia Principal Herald.
