Regarding surveys: a number of years ago, a reporter to a local paper was
invited to attend an event. (This was an out-of-area event for me.  I don't
remember where.)  Rather than just come for two minutes, take pictures and
leave, he came for the entire event, wore loaner garb and stayed for court and
feast.  It was announced that he had a survey that he would like people to take,
strictly on a volunteer basis.  He had fifty copies of the survey.  He ran out.
I don't remember all of the questions and results (a brief summary was posted
