I suggest that the PROPER solution is to use large unglazed earthenware
containers and splash water on the outside of them on hot days. Slightly
more practical would be to take a wicker basket and line it with a layer of
open cell foam. Keep all food in water tight containers, and wet the foam
thoroughly every morning. Throw a wet towel over the basket too.

The idea is to use evaporative cooling to stop things from baking dry and the
formation of condensation on the inside of the sealed bags.

