Meat, vegetable or fruit pies need to be either hermetically sealed or
refrigerated or they will turn bad with horrifying speed. In period, food
was preserved by keeping it in honey, vinegar or brine. The other way was
to bake all of the mosture out, e.g. jerky, pasta and hard bread. Much labour
would be needed to turn such foods into attractive meals.

