>bagpipes at 7:00 in the morning?) almost any form of
>entertainment would usually be greatly appreciated. Good Luck!!
 
As an aside, I unintentionally learned one answer this past weekend. Having
become irreversibly awake at 6 AM, and after performing the morning's
ablutions, I was left with little do to for a couple hours, and about 7 AM
decided it would be a good idea to get a jump on the day's piping by working
over my (ailing) pipes.
 
To this end I departed camp, passing fen and forest, to a distance that my
experience said would be safe, where I could not possibly be heard at all in
camp, and proceeded to warm and tune them up. Unfortunately I was not aware
of the rather unusual acoustics of the area at that hour which caused the 
pipes to be heard clearly through the entire camp!
 
I became aware of this unfortunate turn of events after a Scot showed up and
informed me that he, on the furthest end of the encampment, had been roused
by the sound of the pipes and what a wonderful way to be awakened it was!
 
With some embarrassment I quit and returned to camp, to be greeted by all and 
sundry with compliments on the fine playing, and all apologies of mine were 
simply waved away. To be sure, I suspect that those who don't care for the
pipes merely kept silent, but I appreciated the comment from one woman who 
had been up all night tending her horse: She was just getting to sleep, heard 
the pipes and thought, "Oh ****, what idiot is playing bagpipes at this 
hour...  wait, that's not half-bad... that's really nice... zzzzZZZZZ..".
 
Later in the day I tested the acoustics of the area, and found that the sound
of the pipes wouldn't carry even a quarter of the distance it apparently did
that early morning, that it carried only about as far as my normal experience
indicated. (Valuing my hide, I ran no more tests of early morning acoustics.)
 
I guess the lessons in this are:
  There is appreciation for an instrument played reasonably well, *
  Beware of treacherous acoustics :-), and,
  Playing bagpipes at 7AM is not invariably fatal! **
 
 
Chaluim Dearg
 
---
