For what it's worth, allow me to supply some background.

The move to formally organize scouting in the East springs from the
general requirement that anyone participating in combat must be
authorized by the Marshallate.  It has been brewing for about two
years, and is remarkably poorly organized.  I strongly recommend that
you (and anyone else with a legitimate opinion) boil your comments
down to a presentable letter, and send it to the King, the Earl
Marshall, and the Captain of Scouts.  I personally have been
suggesting that scout authorization be viewed as part of the job of
the marshallate, and that the same philosphical standards apply, i.e.,
safety first.  Unfortunately, there have been deeply political
arguments involved with this thing, the upshot of which has been that
the six or seven people actually doing the work have not been given
any guidance at all.

Curia did require that anyone participating in combat (fighters,
scouts, combat archers, etc.) be at least 18 years old or be an
emancipated minor.  However, there is no grounds for requiring proof
of membership to be a scout or a fighter or anything except an officer
of the SCA.  This point particularly should be brought to the
attention of the appropriate Kingdom officers, because somebody has
really gotten their info mixed up.
