seem to have gotten lost in transmission. Thus, I'm posting them directly to
the mailing list. If you see them twice, my apologies.]

Greetings, gentles all!

Danulf (the moderator of SCAnet) and I are beginning to work on creating an
electronic Domesday Boke, a sort of "phone book" for SCAdians on the net. To
this end, I am putting out a call for entries. The items to be in the book are
the following:

1) SCA and mundane names
2) SCA and mundane locations (ie, shire & kingdom, town & state, zip)
3) Titles and offices (*briefly*; 1/2 line max!)
4) net address (Inter/ARPAnet format strongly preferred)
5) Interests (*briefly*; one line maximum!)
6) Are you/do you want to be on the SCA mailing list? (which you probably
   already are, since you're reading this).
7) Do you want your address publically known? 

Note that this is the same information that Danulf requests for joining the
mailing list. This is no coincidence: we are planning to merge our databases.
Thus, if you have already sent all of this information to Danulf, there is no
need to send it to me; I'll be getting it from him.

The only fields that are *required* for entry in the Domesday are SCA name and
net address. All other fields are optional, but encouraged.

Note that mundane location does not mean full address; I will not enter full
addresses if I receive them. This is just so that people can get some feeling
for where the people that they are communicating with are from.

If you have many titles, try to trim them down to the most important ones.
The order of the ETC is well known and respected, and covers a lot.

Please keep your net address brief. If the only way to get to you is via
UUCP bang address (ie, x!y!justin), then pick one or two *good* paths, and
put those in. I will likely keep net addresses down to one line, and I will
*certainly* not take more than two lines. Thus, complex Usenet graphs will
*not* be accepted. Choose one from the backbone that works well.

I'm assuming that most people will answer "yes" to #7. If you really want
an unlisted address, tell me, and I'll put you in the database, but not
the published book. To a certain degree, I'm willing to act as a clearing-
house for these unlisted addresses, but don't abuse it.

The book will be distributed via the net once we're finished, probably in
a month or three. I'll probably make a limited number of printed copies
to sell at events for a nominal fee, for people whose net access is 
erratic.

Questions? Suggestions? Entries (I hope!)? Send them to me! Please *don't*
put your entries on the net, unless you absolutely can't get through to
me.

See ya'll in the yellow pages...

