SInce my lord competed in the Midrealm crown, I know for a fact
that Mistress Myrra checked all the memberships of the unbelted
fighters and prospective consorts when (then) His Highness
submitted his list of unbelted invitees, and checked the
memberships of the Chivalry who reserved when they sent their
letters in (two weeks in advance). This enabled her to contact
folks who were expired and let them gracefully withdraw early,
rather than being turned down at the list table., Some Chivals
who were affected this way were Count Fuyuzuru, Sir Dag, and one
or two others.
 
Memberships are handled in this way:
 
Checks are received and journalized in the first twenty days of
the month. The last ten days of the month are reserved for
late-arriving checks, and for finalizing data-entry of the new
and renewed memberships. Sometime between the 25th and the first
of the next month the database is updated and the new memberships
are "run". This creates a list of folks whose memberships will be
current as of the first of the NEXT month. For example:
 
My membership expires Nov. 1 of 1988. I should send a check to
the Registry by September 15th. That check will be journalized,
my entry in the database will be updated, and my name will appear
on the list which is printed October first. This list contains
the names of people who have valid memberships as of Nov. 1. If I
do not send my check 6 weeks in advance, my membership will
lapse. The reason for this lag time is the need to print
newsletter labels in advance.
 
The mailing labels for each month are run between the 5th and the
10th of the month PRECEEDING the cover date of the newsletter.
They are mailed priority mail to the CHroniclers so they arrive
