In the past few weeks several people have expressed interest in brewing mead.
Here are a couple references that I'm aware of:

	Title:	Brewing Mead/Wassail! In Mazers of Mead
	Authors:	Gayre & Papazian
	Publisher:	Brewers Publications
	ISBN:	0-937381-00-4

This is actually two books in one. The first part is a reprint of the book
"Wassail! In Mazers of Mead" by Lt. Colonet Robert Gayre, which is considered by
many to be the definitive history of the beverage mead. The second part is new,
called "Brewing Mead". This is a few short chapters on how to brew mead,
including some simple recipes.

Also, in the Winter 1987 issue of Zymurgy (vol. 10. no. 5) there is an article
titled "The Art of Making Mead" by Brother Adam. This is reprinted from his book
on beekeeping. The article is kinda technical, but very informative.

/Don
