Over the last few weeks a great deal of SCA news has come across this net.
Having a national communications net is a wonderful way of getting news out,
stories shared, and knowledge distributed. Unfortunately, something not so
wonderful is happening. The knives are going in deep and personal attacks
are being made. We are forgetting the main idea of the society,
HONOR. There will always be politics and problems, but making attacks on 
people not plugged into the net and unable to defend themselves is hardly
worthy of a group pledged to honor. 

Lately, there have been some complaints about fencing in the East Kingdom,
and some of the Kingdom's fencing rules. We are not saying they are perfect,
but we are having trouble getting most of the marshalls to respond to letters
or come to meetings at events. If you have a beef with "an un-named and un-local
but highly placed marshall", and if your facts are correct, confront this 
person face to face in an honorable way, not behind his back on a national net.

As for complaints about not being able to feed into the rules, and the
allegation that only a small group is controlling them, why have there
never been responses to the letters that have been sent to the marshalls
asking for your input to controversial rule changes? Why are the marshalls
not polling their local fencers then bringing those responses to the
marshall meetings called at events (at least send them in). The letters
started going out because there has not been great attendance at the meetings,
so the thought was send out questions and get responses. What else can be done?
Every marshall gets a copy of the rules after changes, and letters before the
changes from those wanting input. The communication paths have been open, use
them. We have had people interested in starting a kingdom fencing newsletter
to share event ideas and fencing tips, but due to non-response from the
marshallate letters sent, figure why try?

We are sorry to air our bad linen on the net, but some folks in the East
seem to forget that this small population they are complaining about got
fencing recongnized in the East. It wasn't easy, but finally there is a
structure and set of rules that were acceptable to the crown and BoD, we
have to start somewhere. Some minor points like titles and that have yet
to be ironed out, but at least we are FENCING! Instead of poking flames
at people who do not have access to the net, we should be helping to tweak
and hone this infant system. Most of all, FENCE AND HAVE FUN, that's what
it is really all about (isn't it?).

For anyone out there interested in a set of our rules and order the June
Pikestaff tells you how to get them (sorry they are not in ascii form for
email). We in the East also have great ides for fencing events and tournaments.
I don't know about you folks but some of the role playing tourneys have been
a blast! Let's share some of the good with the bad, OK?

					Mharie Obridge na Druiminach and
					Balatair la Roder

Pat Corl
