Subject: Reorganize Power within the SCA
Message-Id: <11043@steinmetz.ge.com>


  It seems here in the East matters have gotten a tad unpleasant.
  Things have been resolved, and I am not in the minority in
  praising the honor and nobility of our King and Queen, and
  the other principles in the affair. But enough on the past.
  This incident wasn't a problem in itself, so much as it is
  a SYMPTOM of a problem.

  It's time to decentralize power and responsibility in the SCA.

  The current system of obtaining membership is too slow. There
  is a better way.

  Why not allow the exchequer of any SCA group accept payment
  for and issue membership cards for the SCA ? Then the
  exchequer would send the new members names and their payment to
  the regional, principality or kingdom exchequer. Kingdom
  would extract that part of the payment needed for TI and
  BoD maintenance, and send it to the BoD, while keeping
  that part of the money associated with kingdom newsletters,
  and kingdom overhead. Kingdom would maintain a computerized
  list of members of the kingdom, and would periodically forward
  this list to the BoD and it's brother kingdoms.

  Exchequers would have spare copies of kingdom newsletters
  sent to them each month, which they would forward to new
  members not on the kingdom mailing list. This way, new members
  can immediately find out what's going on.

  I believe the fighter's registry is handled by kingdom ?
  If not it should be as well !

  The BoD still has a place in the SCA, as a handler of mundane
  affairs and a unifying influence between kingdoms, especially
  through its publication of Tournaments Illuminated.

  But the time has come for power to move closer to the people,
  and what better place than the persons and officers of our
  King and Queen ? I think most of the 1900 paid members of the
  East Kingdom probably agree with this.

                 The Fair and Gracious Lord Spud
       ( yes, I am OFFICIALLY Fair and Gracious, and a Lord )
