wearing was a light gambeson and all I got was a welt. The only
thing that I have ever had happen was when two new fighters got
a little cranked up (easy to do with such light weapons!!) and one
got hit on the elbow when his pad slid down. His elbow was
tender for a couple of days but that was it.
     This form imitates kitana and therefore assuming you are 
wearing silken robes at best makes for very little contact required.
Fighting shinai helped my great sword technique a lot although
you should always fight light first then fight heavy. It can be
very difficult to calibrate down.
