Ooh!  Ooh!  See here, "Poor Mundane", don't let the prevalence of fighters
scare you off the SCA.  The Society needs more like you and your wife.
As for camping, I would go ahead and take my standard large tent, but not 
pitch it directly adjacent to the eric (where the fighting goes on); later
on, you can build a nice big pavillion with little difficulty (mail me
privately and tell me your USnail address, and I'll send you some patterns).
As for your camping gear, here are a few hints: put a nice rug over your
ice chest; buy a few yards of decent-looking fake fur to cover your
sleeping bags.  Unfortunately, I can't think of any way to camouflage a
Coleman lantern that would still allow it to function; I prefer hurricane
oil lamps or alpinists' candle lanterns (neither strictly period, but still
look nice and have the right atmosphere); later on, you can make candle
lanterns out of perforated tin (if you're doing 1600's, that should be
close enough to your period for authenticity).

But the point of the Society (or so this optimist believes) is to have fun.
People should (and hopefully will) be patient with you as you get used to
the atmosphere.  They'll really appreciate the harping and (especially if
you're good) the piping (hint: don't pipe at 5am!).

Enjoy!
Siobhan ni hEodhusa


