Just two quick comments --

Yes, Christopher Stasheff didn't find out about the SCA until after writing
The Warlock in Spite of Himself. *However*, he was so taken by the Society
that he appears to have immediately gone out and written a book about it,
called Escape Velocity, which is a prequel to Warlock. Sadly, Escape Velocity
isn't anywhere near as good a book as Warlock; I'd only recommend it to SCA
completists. The group in it isn't the SCA, but it's clearly based on an
outside view of the Society.

Regarding the portrayal of the Horde in Murder at the War, I must agree with
David le Casse that they were somewhat misshown. It seemed to me that Margaret
blended the Horde and Tuchux into one group, to the extent of attributing
several stories that I have always heard as being Tuchux stunts to the Horde.
It was the only major flaw I found in the book (aside from the normal problems
of a first novel), but it did bother me a fair amount.

						-- Justin du Coeur

