SCA politics.  My Lord Benicoeur, you seemed to suggest that the discussion
concerning paganism and the Society would be inappropriate for an open
environment.  How can you justify this?  Obviously, paganism is a part
of the SCA.  Is this something that you feel we need to be ashamed of,
and should attempt to conceal from anyone not a part of the Society?
And what else should we attempt to hide?

I just cannot see any circumstances where censorship is justified.  I
can think of many instances where it can be destructive.  The Society
is supposed to be a place where we don't have to deal with the mundane
world, a place where people respect each other and each other's
judgements, and where we don't have to worry about what people are
going to say, because we know that they won't try to hurt us or our
friends.  If we think it becomes necessary to censor ourselves, we've
lost these ideals.

