	Lady Bevin Fraser of Stirling (aka Katherine Kurtz) attended her first
Society event at the Founding Tourney of the Barony of the Angels in the summer
of A.S. 6.
	Marion Zimmer Bradley showed up in Berkeley from New York in 1971 also,
but may have been involved with the Society before that -- she is the older
sister of Master Edwin Berseark (Paul Zimmer), who was certainly part of the
original Society.
	Sir Bela of Eastmarch (Poul Anderson) was certainly an early member,
but was not, I believe, at any of the first 3 or 4 Tourneys, at least according
to the stories I heard at Hightower (Randall Garrett's Society household).

	Since the early Society and Science Fiction Fandom shared an
overlapping membership (to the Society's detriment -- fannish politics almost
destroyed the Society several times), most S.F. writers have bee involved in or
exposed to the Society, including Jerry Pournelle (Jerome, Laird o' McKenna),
and Harlan Ellison (who had 30-some fighters' gloved dropped at his feet for
making an off-hand remark about the Society at an S.F. Con once).
	Peter Beagle has a dealy accurate eye for Society foibles indeed!
