Subject:  Fencing


The normal test we use on fencing blades is to deliberately bend it,
say by thrusting against the floor, and then to see if it holds a
bend.  This of course will not find all blades before they break, but
it does tend to get blades which show obvious signs of metal fatigue
out of circulation.  As with all sports, we can't make fencing 100%
safe, we can only try to eliminate the accidents that could have been
avoided.  After all, even crossing the street is a risky proposition
these days.

