I am Jas Clarion, Master of Fence for the BMDL
(Barony Marche of the Debatable Lands - Pittsburgh).

I cannot more heartily applaud Elektra's post on fencing.
I fence both mundanely and in the Society and I too (as well as others
 here) have noticed the rising calibration levels in fencing in the Society.

In fact an interesting situation occured during a bout at a tourney in the
BMDL, where an un-named (and un-local, but highly placed) marshal
observed his student bearing an epee and facing one of our newer fencers,
who was using a foil.  After the bout when the student noted that all she
could feel were "slappy slappy things" the marshal said
"Yeah, at the next rules-meeting we are going to have to get around to banning
foils.  With all the armor we are wearing now days you just can't feel 'em."

I was rather appalled by this comment and also rather scared...
Currently I think our (BMDL) fencers have the lowest calibration in the East
(with possible exceptions on the East coast where I haven't had the chance
 to fence much).  Where are we going???
Are we fated to go down the same path as heavy-weapons????
I have also fought rattan, and I will again in the BMDL - with people I know.
However I KNOW that I don't want to get hit with blows that I have often
