insurance companies are wont to do.  These included the numbers of
people participating, the injuries *commonly* received, and how often
these sorts of injuries are received.  Canadian sports insurance 
recognizes four categories of danger or risk in sports.  The first is 
chess, board games, etc. where risk is very low.  The second group 
includes curling, golf, and such sports where injuries exist but are 
uncommon(this is where the ping pong came in).  the third group includes
such sports as basketball, baseball, and football, where injuries are
relatively common and deaths are not unheard of.  The fourth group 
includes skydiving, shark-wrestling:-) and sports which are considered 
quite hazardous.  I apologize if my posting made SCA fighting seem 
