This is partially a response to Elektra's comments about injuries in
fencing and a plea for some help.

There have actually been several major injuries including one more
death.  That was; however, caused by an electrical malfunction wherin
a 220 volt line managed to cross the B of a weapon. Grounded on sweat
and the fencer was electrocuted.  That is why all major international
competitions are run using 12Volt batteries to power the scoring boxes
and optoisolation is used for overhead scoring towers.  In the US we
tend to use GFCI isolated circuits to give a margin of safety.

The plea I am making is to watch for old and battered masks.  There
exists a standard test for the strenght of mask mesh and it should be
used.

The test consists of attempting to broach the mesh with a punch of
carefully controlled size and force.  I intend to bring several to the
Pensic War. If you want details or a dealers name please contact me.
I have access to enough punchs so some can be loaned to list folk for 
